unfortunately, from what I understand, the only way to get into an open lab section is by dropping and adding the class with the new section.  If you were already registered, you could use the Option option in the CalCentral enrollment interface to switch sections.   Labs you do have to sign up for in CalCentral for EE16A/B.

Looking at 16A right now, I'll bet they added seats recently.  There are 157 waitlisted, and I'll bet all of them are waitlisted because they are registered for a lab that is full.  There are 150+ openings now, so it's gotta be because of that.  If you dropped and added back into one of the lab sections with open seats, I'll bet you can get in right now.  (Use 999 for the discussion).

This is the right answer. You need to drop the class and re-add with a lab that has open seats.  Otherwise, you just sit there.

Hi, I am a sophomore intended CS major waitlisted for EE16A right now. From what I hear, I am more likely than not going to get into the class (i.e. lecture and discussion), but I am wondering about the protocol of getting into a lab section.

The current lab section I am waitlisted for (section 102) has 0 open seats, and I am not sure whether I'd make it into this lab. If I do not get into this specific lab, how do I switch to an open lab section later on? Alternatively, am I able to change to an open lab on CalCentral now without losing my current waitlist position for the lecture? I am not sure whether this is something to be done on CalCentral anytime soon, or if it is the type of thing to be arranged with TA's and/or professors once the class already starts.
history.subject: EE16A Lab Waitlist Protocol?
